<p class="c21 c22"><span class="c3">We will split our code into many files so that each file can be worked on individually via GitHub. Each task will be completed at roughly the same time, and nobody is assigned to anything specific. Members will work on whatever files make the most sense to them.</span>
</p>
<p class="c21 c22"><span class="c3">This project has 3 major milestones that come before the first flag where we will decide how to continue our project:</span>
</p>
<ol class="c8 lst-kix_rlc3eo1l2mcp-0 start" start="1">
    <li class="c21 c33 li-bullet-0"><span class="c5">All </span><span class="c3">team members have a decent understanding of Rust. It&rsquo;s very difficult to expand or troubleshoot code you don&rsquo;t understand, so this won&rsquo;t be done in parallel. (6-8 weeks)</span>
    </li>
</ol>
<ol class="c8 lst-kix_rlc3eo1l2mcp-1 start" start="1">
    <li class="c18 li-bullet-0"><span class="c3">We will first make a simple command line program to solve a math problem (&frac12; week)</span>
    </li>
    <li class="c18 li-bullet-0"><span class="c3">We will then use a basic library like Qt to learn how to use libraries in rust (2 weeks)</span>
    </li>
    <li class="c18 li-bullet-0"><span class="c3">We will then use rg3d to make a simple scene to render with a camera that moves (4 weeks)</span>
    </li>
</ol>
<ol class="c8 lst-kix_rlc3eo1l2mcp-0" start="2">
    <li class="c21 c33 li-bullet-0"><span class="c3">A basic movement system will be developed along a flat plane. (2 weeks, done in parallel)</span>
    </li>
</ol>
<ol class="c8 lst-kix_rlc3eo1l2mcp-1 start" start="1">
    <li class="c18 li-bullet-0"><span class="c3">The player should be able to move with WASD, jump with space, and look around with the mouse.</span>
    </li>
    <li class="c18 li-bullet-0"><span
            class="c3">A flat plane should be drawn to allow the player to walk on top of</span></li>
    <li class="c18 li-bullet-0"><span class="c3">Shooting shouldn&rsquo;t have an animation yet, but a bullet should be fired in the center of the screen by clicking with the mouse.</span>
    </li>
</ol>
<ol class="c8 lst-kix_rlc3eo1l2mcp-0" start="3">
    <li class="c21 c33 li-bullet-0"><span class="c3">A full level should be developed (2 weeks, done in parallel)</span>
    </li>
</ol>
<ol class="c8 lst-kix_rlc3eo1l2mcp-1 start" start="1">
    <li class="c18 li-bullet-0"><span class="c3">Enemies should fire at the player</span></li>
    <li class="c18 li-bullet-0"><span class="c3">Enemies should be able to kill the player if the player is shot too many times.</span>
    </li>
    <li class="c18 li-bullet-0"><span class="c3">Enemies should die upon being shot.</span></li>
    <li class="c18 li-bullet-0"><span
            class="c3">There should be places the player must jump on to complete the level</span></li>
    <li class="c18 li-bullet-0"><span class="c3">Basic animations for most actions should be in place</span></li>
</ol>
